{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17499586","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17499586"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:01:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:01:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1519"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1519","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1519"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.6,0.07,0.06,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1519"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"83491"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1519","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1519"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1519"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68364"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"1293"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"3464"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"9644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3557"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10697"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28375"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41380"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"83491","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/83491"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old man presents to his General Practitioner with a two month history of episodic passage of black, tarry stools. Over the same time period he has experienced some weight loss and fatigue. He does not report any abdominal pain or vomiting. His medical history includes hypertension and type 2 diabetes. His medications include perindopril and metformin. He has a 30 pack-year smoking history and drinks 20 standard drinks each week. His complete blood examination shows a microcytic anaemia and an endoscopy is arranged. This is the view of the anterior wall of the body of the stomach (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Gastric MALT lymphoma","Gastrointestinal stromal tumour","Linitis plastica","Gastric varix","Type II neuroendocrine syndrome"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe photograph shows a well-defined mass lesion on the anterior wall of the body of the stomach that is protruding into the lumen. The overlying mucosa is intact apart from an area of ulceration in the middle of the lesion. This is the typical appearance of a \u003Cstrong\u003Egastrointestinal stromal tumour (GIST)\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA GIST is a malignant mesenchymal tumour that arises from interstitial cells of Cajal in the gastrointestinal tract. Some 60% of these are found in the stomach, 35% in the small intestine and 5% elsewhere (colon, rectum, oesophagus or omentum). These tumours often remain asymptomatic and are found incidentally. Large (\u0026gt;2 cm) tumours can present in the sixth decade of life with anaemia and upper gastrointestinal bleeding.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGastric MALT lymphomas \u003C/strong\u003Efrequently present as infiltrative, ulcerated lesions arising from the deep mucosa or submucosa.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELinitis plastica \u003C/strong\u003Eis a type of gastric cancer that commonly occurs in the fundus. It is characterised by thickening of the stomach wall and deformation of the stomach, leading to a \u0027leather bottle-like\u0027 appearance. It is not associated with discrete lesions, as shown in the photograph.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EType II neuroendocrine tumours \u003C/strong\u003Eare associated with Zollinger-Ellison syndrome, which is an acid hypersecretion state triggered by increased gastrin production. Endoscopy in this case would exhibit single or multiple polypoid nodules in the fundus and antrum, with multiple peptic ulcers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGastric varices \u003C/strong\u003Etend to bleed quite severely, often presenting with frank haematemesis, haemodynamic instability (sometimes hypovolaemic shock) and abdominal pain. These often look like serpiginous vascular structures, and are associated with hepatic cirrhosis in the Australian population.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastrointestinal stromal tumours (GIST) are most commonly found in the stomach.","Large GISTs can present with symptoms of anaemia and upper GI bleeding, but they are often found incidentally."],"references":["Wang M, Xu J, Zhang Y, Tu L, Qiu WQ, et al. Gastrointestinal stromal tumor: 15-years\u0027 experience in a single center. BMC Surg. 2014;14:93. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4254179/","Park BS, Lee SH. Endoscopic features aiding the diagnosis of gastric mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue lymphoma. Yeungnam Univ J Med. 2019;36(2):85-91. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6784630/","Parab TM, DeRogatis MJ, Boaz AM, Grasso SA, Issack PS, Duarte DA, Urayeneza O, Vahdat S, Qiao JH, Hinika GS. Gastrointestinal stromal tumors: a comprehensive review. J Gastrointest Oncol. 2019 Feb;10(1):144-154. doi: 10.21037/jgo.2018.08.20. PMID: 30788170; PMCID: PMC6351301. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6351301/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68364"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1519"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"1877"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"1877","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/1877"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ac150d3d-f44b-4c22-9b8c-cc623ad3ee6d.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/ac150d3d-f44b-4c22-9b8c-cc623ad3ee6d.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":544,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68364","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/68364"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-04T20:14:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-04T20:14:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1519"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"83491"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","li